NAME

	_printf -  function that produces output according to a format.


SYNOPSIS

	int _printf(const char *format, ...);

DESCRIPTION

	The _printf function prints a formatted string to the standard ouput (stdout). 
	It takes a format string and a variable number of arguments.

	Supported format specifiers are:

	- %c: character.
	- %s: string.
	- %i/%d: signed decimal integer.
	- %%: the percent character.

RETURN VALUES

	The function returns the total number of characters printed to the standard output.
	In case of error, a negative value may be returned: return (-1);


